WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.101 --> 00:00:08.347
<i>Ah. well done Mrs Dorrit.</i>

2
00:00:08.600 --> 00:00:11.907
<i>a very nice little... girl indeed!</i>

3
00:00:12.160 --> 00:00:15.143
<i>Yes. ah. there's a pretty!</i>

4
00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:18.200
<i>Now. would you care to
hold her. Mr Dorrit?</i>

5
00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:19.894
<i>There. there.</i>

6
00:00:21.713 --> 00:00:23.160
<i>There she is.</i>

7
00:00:23.628 --> 00:00:26.454
<i>The first child of the Marshalsea.
Mr Dorrit.</i>

8
00:00:26.574 --> 00:00:28.802
<i>Now. ain't that a distinction?</i>

9
00:00:33.648 --> 00:00:35.395
<i>A new little Dorrit!</i>

10
00:00:37.422 --> 00:00:38.502
Little Amy!

11
00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

12
00:01:10.481 --> 00:01:13.493
Transcript: Chocolate
Sync: SinkMe & Moochie

13
00:01:29.687 --> 00:01:32.418
- Good morning. Miss Amy.
- Good morning. John.

14
00:02:26.307 --> 00:02:27.426
<i>Flintwinch!</i>

15
00:02:30.490 --> 00:02:32.101
Yeah. I hear you.

16
00:02:32.544 --> 00:02:34.627
You and your blasted stick.

17
00:02:42.578 --> 00:02:44.388
The girl comes this morning?

18
00:02:44.958 --> 00:02:46.049
She does.

19
00:02:46.536 --> 00:02:47.536
Good.

20
00:02:48.290 --> 00:02:49.764
Tell her nothing!

21
00:03:12.866 --> 00:03:14.259
<i>Oh. Lord save us!</i>

22
00:03:17.423 --> 00:03:20.455
Please. ma'am. don't be alarmed.
It's Amy Dorrit.

23
00:03:20.575 --> 00:03:22.516
come to call on Mrs Clennam.

24
00:03:22.636 --> 00:03:25.587
Oh. dear me. Just a moment.

25
00:03:26.742 --> 00:03:27.824
<i>Jeremiah!</i>

26
00:03:27.944 --> 00:03:30.367
<i>Now what. woman?
What's the matter with you? Eh?</i>

27
00:03:30.487 --> 00:03:32.207
<i>- Out of the way!
- Oh!</i>

28
00:03:33.284 --> 00:03:34.335
Yes? What?

29
00:03:35.416 --> 00:03:37.805
Amy Dorrit. sir. to see Mrs Clennam.

30
00:03:38.670 --> 00:03:41.291
Ah. Yes. You'd better come in.

31
00:03:45.466 --> 00:03:48.397
Thank you. sir.
Would I be speaking to Mr Clennam?

32
00:03:49.267 --> 00:03:50.827
No. you would not.

33
00:03:52.412 --> 00:03:54.392
You're very small. ain't you?

34
00:03:54.806 --> 00:03:56.747
Yes. sir. I am strong.

35
00:03:57.205 --> 00:03:58.261
Are you now?

36
00:03:59.231 --> 00:04:01.414
You look a shrimpy little thing to me.

37
00:04:02.842 --> 00:04:05.012
Well. she's upstairs. This way.

38
00:04:17.492 --> 00:04:19.171
It's a bit dark. Sir.

39
00:04:19.291 --> 00:04:21.710
She likes it dark. and I'm used to it.

40
00:04:22.467 --> 00:04:24.332
Not afraid of the dark. I hope?

41
00:04:24.452 --> 00:04:26.298
- No. sir.
- Good girl.

42
00:04:26.418 --> 00:04:29.267
- Not afraid of me either. I hope?
- No. sir.

43
00:04:29.520 --> 00:04:33.022
Well. you ought to be.
cos I'm a terror when I'm roused.

44
00:04:48.160 --> 00:04:49.413
Here we are.

45
00:04:51.159 --> 00:04:52.183
<i>Come.</i>

46
00:04:55.478 --> 00:04:56.662
Here she is.

47
00:04:57.720 --> 00:04:59.067
You won't want me.

48
00:04:59.187 --> 00:05:00.552
No. you can go.

49
00:05:09.383 --> 00:05:11.261
- Amy Dorrit.
- Yes. ma'am.

50
00:05:11.381 --> 00:05:12.650
Come closer.

51
00:05:19.700 --> 00:05:22.547
Why. you're a child!

52
00:05:22.800 --> 00:05:24.502
I'm 21. Mrs Clennam.

53
00:05:25.581 --> 00:05:28.000
I know I am small.
but I am quite grown up.

54
00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:29.167
Are you?

55
00:05:32.636 --> 00:05:35.343
Mr Casby tells me you are looking
for employment.

56
00:05:35.463 --> 00:05:36.480
Yes. ma'am.

57
00:05:38.644 --> 00:05:41.293
I've brought some samples
of my work. ma'am.

58
00:05:47.147 --> 00:05:48.147
Good.

59
00:05:49.792 --> 00:05:51.467
This is good neat work.

60
00:05:53.102 --> 00:05:54.402
Well. Miss Dorrit.

61
00:05:56.001 --> 00:05:58.868
I'm prepared to take you on approval.
General duties.

62
00:05:58.988 --> 00:06:01.798
3 days a week. from 8 in the
morning till 6 in the evening.

63
00:06:01.918 --> 00:06:03.760
7 and 6 a week with all found.

64
00:06:03.920 --> 00:06:05.800
You may start this very day.
Will that suit?

65
00:06:05.960 --> 00:06:07.984
Yes. ma'am.
very well. ma'am. thank you...

66
00:06:08.104 --> 00:06:09.738
You'll find it quiet here.

67
00:06:09.858 --> 00:06:13.440
There's only myself and Flintwinch
and his wife. My husband and son...

68
00:06:16.255 --> 00:06:19.074
My husband and son are abroad.

69
00:06:34.387 --> 00:06:35.638
<i>Arthur...</i>

70
00:06:36.738 --> 00:06:37.871
<i>Put it right.</i>

71
00:06:39.909 --> 00:06:41.080
<i>Put it right...</i>

72
00:06:42.622 --> 00:06:44.280
<i>Put it right... Put it right.</i>

73
00:06:45.233 --> 00:06:46.667
Well. Mr Clennam!

74
00:06:47.968 --> 00:06:50.289
Not long left of our deuced confinement!

75
00:06:50.847 --> 00:06:54.627
What a fate! To be quarantined in
Marseilles. of all places!

76
00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:57.040
- And for what?
- For no very good reason...

77
00:06:57.200 --> 00:06:58.791
Except we've travelled from the East.

78
00:06:58.911 --> 00:07:01.250
and the East is the country of
the plague. so they think.

79
00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:04.613
The East? You call Venice
the East? Do they?

80
00:07:05.067 --> 00:07:07.560
Mr Clennam has been in China. Papa.

81
00:07:07.680 --> 00:07:09.427
He's been away for 15 years.

82
00:07:09.946 --> 00:07:12.400
I'm sure he can put up with
a few more hours delay.

83
00:07:12.642 --> 00:07:15.090
Besides. I've enjoying the company here.

84
00:07:15.210 --> 00:07:19.062
Oh. the company!
Well. excellent company. to be sure!

85
00:07:19.907 --> 00:07:21.867
Thank you. Mr Clennam...

86
00:07:21.987 --> 00:07:25.187
We've enjoyed these days together.
haven't we. Tattycoram?

87
00:07:25.471 --> 00:07:26.504
Yes. Miss.

88
00:07:29.040 --> 00:07:30.584
It's getting so hot!

89
00:07:31.210 --> 00:07:33.578
Tatty. would you carry my shawl for me?

90
00:07:39.080 --> 00:07:40.281
I hate you.

91
00:07:40.401 --> 00:07:43.760
All of you. hate you. hate you with
your kindness and your charity

92
00:07:43.983 --> 00:07:47.952
and your pretty faces and your baby
names. like I was a toy or a doll...

93
00:07:54.587 --> 00:07:57.025
Papa. shall we join Mamma downstairs?

94
00:07:57.145 --> 00:07:59.919
No. no you go ahead. Pet.
I'll follow on.

95
00:08:00.479 --> 00:08:03.469
- � bientot. Mr Clennam!
- A presto. Miss Meagles.

96
00:08:07.423 --> 00:08:10.290
You have a very lovely
daughter. Mr Meagles.

97
00:08:10.410 --> 00:08:13.848
Yes. yes. I do. And Mrs Meagles
and I are very glad you think so.

98
00:08:13.968 --> 00:08:16.347
Mr Clennam. very glad indeed.

99
00:08:28.544 --> 00:08:29.976
There you are.

100
00:08:31.227 --> 00:08:33.254
Why are you always following me?

101
00:08:34.292 --> 00:08:36.227
Go away! You don't care for me!

102
00:08:36.347 --> 00:08:39.067
Oh. but I do... Harriet.

103
00:08:41.183 --> 00:08:43.122
They're waiting for you.

104
00:08:44.253 --> 00:08:45.591
I won't come.

105
00:08:47.166 --> 00:08:50.019
I'll run away.
Or I'll curl up and die here.

106
00:08:50.139 --> 00:08:51.425
No. you won't.

107
00:08:51.907 --> 00:08:53.959
You'll be patient. and bear it all.

108
00:08:54.079 --> 00:08:57.187
I thought they took me in
to be part of their family but.

109
00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.309
they treat me like dirt.

110
00:09:01.342 --> 00:09:02.721
Like I was nothing!

111
00:09:02.841 --> 00:09:04.387
Well. of course they do.

112
00:09:09.255 --> 00:09:10.747
I was like you once.

113
00:09:13.131 --> 00:09:15.787
No... Go away. I'm frightened of you.

114
00:09:16.602 --> 00:09:17.840
And why is that?

115
00:09:21.449 --> 00:09:23.201
You see right through me...

116
00:09:24.699 --> 00:09:26.679
you see all my badness.

117
00:09:28.285 --> 00:09:32.227
You make me worse. you make me
say things I don't mean...

118
00:09:33.211 --> 00:09:34.800
I... I don't hate them.

119
00:09:37.507 --> 00:09:41.027
They're good and kind. and I'm
a wicked thankless creature.

120
00:09:42.440 --> 00:09:44.107
Have it your own way.

121
00:09:45.753 --> 00:09:49.699
Here is my address.
If ever you want to come to me...

122
00:09:52.286 --> 00:09:53.433
you may.

123
00:10:09.634 --> 00:10:12.826
- Thank you Mr Flintwinch.
- 8 o'clock tomorrow. then.

124
00:10:13.664 --> 00:10:14.696
Hold on.

125
00:10:15.955 --> 00:10:18.827
Where do we send to
if we need to get word to you?

126
00:10:20.880 --> 00:10:24.707
Care of Mr Plornish. Bleeding Heart
Yard. if you please. Mr Flintwinch.

127
00:10:24.827 --> 00:10:25.922
Good day.

128
00:10:46.113 --> 00:10:48.311
Didn't care to divulge her address.

129
00:10:48.431 --> 00:10:50.187
Nor would you. I dare say.

130
00:10:50.307 --> 00:10:52.855
if you lived in
a debtor's prison. Flintwinch.

131
00:10:52.975 --> 00:10:54.989
Plenty of people in debtors' prisons.

132
00:10:55.109 --> 00:10:57.862
Some of them even deserve to be there.

133
00:10:57.982 --> 00:11:01.001
God has brought this child to my door.

134
00:11:02.024 --> 00:11:04.045
I cannot avert my eyes.

135
00:11:13.315 --> 00:11:16.599
Our boat is here. We're free at last.

136
00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:19.806
And you're bound for London. Mr Clennam?

137
00:11:19.926 --> 00:11:22.610
Yes. Some necessary business
to settle first.

138
00:11:22.730 --> 00:11:23.747
And then?

139
00:11:23.867 --> 00:11:26.040
And then. I'm going to start my
life all over again.

140
00:11:26.374 --> 00:11:27.387
Well. now!

141
00:11:29.212 --> 00:11:30.907
Oh. at last Tatty!

142
00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:33.147
You can help me with these boxes.

143
00:11:34.005 --> 00:11:36.901
Miss Wade. can I offer you any
assistance in your arrangements?

144
00:11:37.021 --> 00:11:40.551
I'm obliged to you.
but I prefer to go my own way

145
00:11:40.808 --> 00:11:42.363
and in my own manner.

146
00:11:44.145 --> 00:11:47.707
Well. goodbye Miss Wade!
I suppose we may never meet again.

147
00:11:49.320 --> 00:11:50.778
In our course through life

148
00:11:50.898 --> 00:11:54.440
we will meet the people who are
coming to meet us. Mr Meagles.

149
00:11:55.624 --> 00:11:58.240
They may be coming thousands
of miles over the sea;

150
00:11:59.070 --> 00:12:01.158
they may be close at hand now;

151
00:12:02.120 --> 00:12:04.547
they may be coming. for all you know.

152
00:12:05.002 --> 00:12:08.019
from the vilest sweepings
of this very town.

153
00:12:09.125 --> 00:12:10.125
Goodbye.

154
00:12:15.095 --> 00:12:16.198
Sacrebleu!

155
00:12:23.632 --> 00:12:25.885
What a hell hole this place is!

156
00:12:30.335 --> 00:12:33.558
And I a gentleman. born to command.

157
00:12:35.195 --> 00:12:38.067
- Sens'altro. signore.
- Sens'altro signore.

158
00:12:39.167 --> 00:12:40.218
Imbecile.

159
00:12:41.623 --> 00:12:42.879
What a fate!

160
00:12:44.272 --> 00:12:46.907
To be locked up
with a petty smuggler and I.

161
00:12:48.307 --> 00:12:51.056
a distinguished... murderer.

162
00:12:51.535 --> 00:12:52.960
Altro. signore. Altro.

163
00:12:53.120 --> 00:12:55.174
Altro. signore!

164
00:12:57.910 --> 00:13:01.427
I could murder you. here and now.

165
00:13:03.645 --> 00:13:05.387
What do you say. hmm?

166
00:13:06.445 --> 00:13:08.507
Two for the price of one. hmm?

167
00:13:10.265 --> 00:13:11.680
Little Cavalletto.

168
00:13:14.632 --> 00:13:17.093
You think I killed my wife
for her money?

169
00:13:19.384 --> 00:13:21.719
I would have killed her for nothing!

170
00:13:23.309 --> 00:13:26.094
But can they prove it? I think not!

171
00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:29.440
I have laid out a little
money. here and there...

172
00:13:31.268 --> 00:13:33.427
# Qu'est-qui passe ici si tard.

173
00:13:35.563 --> 00:13:37.667
# Compagnons de la marjolaine...

174
00:13:40.946 --> 00:13:42.557
# Qu'est-ce qui passe...

175
00:13:48.280 --> 00:13:49.541
# ici si tard...

176
00:13:51.045 --> 00:13:53.052
# gai. gai. toujours gai! #

177
00:14:28.635 --> 00:14:30.205
Thank you. Mr Chivery.

178
00:14:33.550 --> 00:14:35.667
Ah. all well Miss Amy?

179
00:14:35.787 --> 00:14:37.476
Very well. thank you John.

180
00:14:38.736 --> 00:14:41.068
I got the job with that Mrs Clennams.

181
00:14:41.188 --> 00:14:42.880
But. please. not to tell father.

182
00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:44.707
Whatever you say. Amy.

183
00:14:49.175 --> 00:14:50.349
Well. I'll...

184
00:14:51.074 --> 00:14:53.444
Ah! Ah... I looked in
on your father. Amy.

185
00:14:53.564 --> 00:14:56.750
He... he was fretting a bit. asking
where you were. I... I told him.

186
00:14:56.870 --> 00:15:00.761
you'd be along very soon.
and that calmed him.

187
00:15:00.881 --> 00:15:02.993
Thank you. John.
that's very kind of you.

188
00:15:03.113 --> 00:15:04.827
I better go to him.

189
00:15:09.827 --> 00:15:11.015
Oh. Pa!

190
00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:14.596
I know. son. I know.

191
00:15:35.931 --> 00:15:36.931
Father?

192
00:15:37.457 --> 00:15:39.682
- It's Amy.
- Amy...

193
00:15:40.520 --> 00:15:43.627
Where have you been?
You know I don't like to be left.

194
00:15:44.421 --> 00:15:46.475
But you've been well
looked after. Father.

195
00:15:46.595 --> 00:15:48.413
Mr Chivery and John look after you.

196
00:15:48.533 --> 00:15:50.787
Yes. I suppose.
But it isn't satisfactory.

197
00:15:50.907 --> 00:15:52.800
They have others to
look after besides me.

198
00:15:53.078 --> 00:15:55.337
What if I were to choke or have a fit.

199
00:15:55.457 --> 00:15:58.318
sink down in a swoon with no-one by?

200
00:15:58.916 --> 00:16:00.147
And. you know...

201
00:16:00.526 --> 00:16:04.008
I don't always feel they afford
me the respect that is due to me.

202
00:16:04.128 --> 00:16:05.827
I am sure they do. Father.

203
00:16:06.080 --> 00:16:08.160
I am the Father of the
Marshalsea. you know?

204
00:16:08.280 --> 00:16:09.880
An honorary title. to be sure.

205
00:16:10.057 --> 00:16:13.827
but I fancy it carries a certain
weight. a certain gravitas.

206
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:15.861
Only this morning. while you were out.

207
00:16:15.981 --> 00:16:19.005
a very well-connected gentleman
who was visiting the establishment.

208
00:16:19.125 --> 00:16:21.587
upon hearing of me
asked to be introduced

209
00:16:21.855 --> 00:16:23.600
to the Father of the Marshalsea.

210
00:16:23.987 --> 00:16:25.920
I thought that was very
considerate of him.

211
00:16:26.267 --> 00:16:28.622
Very considerate. very civil.

212
00:16:29.375 --> 00:16:30.796
Where did you go?

213
00:16:33.301 --> 00:16:35.627
I went to call upon a lady. Father.

214
00:16:35.747 --> 00:16:38.787
- Just a social call?
- Yes. Father. just a social call.

215
00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:40.915
You weren't able to leave a card.

216
00:16:41.035 --> 00:16:44.480
She didn't ask for one. Father.
It didn't arise. it wasn't necessary.

217
00:16:45.390 --> 00:16:47.336
She understood you were a lady?

218
00:16:47.579 --> 00:16:51.535
She understood that my daughter is
a lady. the daughter of a gentleman.

219
00:16:51.655 --> 00:16:54.960
- as good a lady as any other lady?
- Yes. Father. I'm sure she did.

220
00:16:57.529 --> 00:16:59.720
Father. I am to go to her 3 days a week.

221
00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:02.023
- But not to work!
- No.

222
00:17:02.897 --> 00:17:04.720
I think she needs companionship. Father.

223
00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:07.027
I need companionship!!

224
00:17:07.147 --> 00:17:08.867
Of course you do. Father.

225
00:17:08.987 --> 00:17:12.898
but Mr Chivery is here. and John.
and you have so many visitors.

226
00:17:13.261 --> 00:17:16.629
I never see Fanny. I never see Edward.
and now I am never to see you!

227
00:17:16.749 --> 00:17:18.799
It is only 3 days a week. Father.

228
00:17:20.325 --> 00:17:21.747
It is necessary.

229
00:17:27.649 --> 00:17:28.649
Yes.

230
00:17:29.929 --> 00:17:30.929
Yes.

231
00:17:31.971 --> 00:17:33.309
I understand.

232
00:17:35.987 --> 00:17:38.427
Now. what shall I get you
for your supper?

233
00:17:40.913 --> 00:17:42.156
Oh. Amy.

234
00:17:43.467 --> 00:17:45.833
I have brought disgrace upon us all.

235
00:17:45.953 --> 00:17:47.751
No. you haven't. Father.

236
00:17:48.147 --> 00:17:51.096
<i>We all love you and we are
all very proud of you.</i>

237
00:17:51.480 --> 00:17:53.307
and everyone here looks up to you.

238
00:17:53.427 --> 00:17:57.283
But it is not as it was meant to be.
You have known nothing else

239
00:17:57.587 --> 00:18:01.057
but if you had known me
as I was before I came here.

240
00:18:01.942 --> 00:18:04.563
as I was before you were born...

241
00:18:05.827 --> 00:18:07.427
I love you as you are.

242
00:18:22.269 --> 00:18:23.457
<i>Arthur...</i>

243
00:18:26.171 --> 00:18:27.987
<i>Your mother. Arthur.</i>

244
00:18:29.450 --> 00:18:33.191
<i>Put it right. Your mother. Arthur.</i>

245
00:18:34.761 --> 00:18:36.171
<i>Your mother...</i>

246
00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:39.240
- Chops to your satisfaction. sir?
- Yes. thank you.

247
00:18:39.360 --> 00:18:41.831
Anything further. sir?
Plum pudding. glass of port. claret?

248
00:18:41.951 --> 00:18:43.758
- Nothing else.
- Clear the table. sir?

249
00:18:43.878 --> 00:18:45.821
- Am I incommoding you?
- Not at all. sir.

250
00:18:45.941 --> 00:18:48.640
Pleasure to serve you. sir.
Stay as long as you like.

251
00:18:48.822 --> 00:18:52.820
I've been putting off going somewhere I
don't particularly want to go. you see.

252
00:18:53.039 --> 00:18:56.715
And. er. where might that be. sir.
if you don't mind me asking. sir?

253
00:18:57.707 --> 00:18:59.736
- Home.
- Right you are. sir.

254
00:18:59.856 --> 00:19:02.722
Leave you till tomorrow. sir?
Care to inspect a bedroom. sir?

255
00:19:02.842 --> 00:19:03.842
No.

256
00:19:04.547 --> 00:19:05.547
Yes.

257
00:19:05.941 --> 00:19:09.667
Chaymaid! Gentleman at table
number 7 wishes to see a room!

258
00:19:09.897 --> 00:19:10.897
Stay!

259
00:19:11.789 --> 00:19:13.933
I've changed my mind. I'll go home.

260
00:19:15.307 --> 00:19:18.833
Chaymaid! Gentleman at table number 7
not going to sleep here.

261
00:19:18.953 --> 00:19:20.008
Going home!

262
00:19:46.018 --> 00:19:48.627
Oh! Oh. Lord. save us!

263
00:20:05.587 --> 00:20:09.347
- Flintwinch. You haven't changed.
- Arthur?

264
00:20:11.953 --> 00:20:13.100
Mr Arthur.

265
00:20:14.152 --> 00:20:17.027
Well. I suppose
you'd better come in.

266
00:20:30.313 --> 00:20:32.267
You'd better let me go first.

267
00:20:32.387 --> 00:20:35.429
Shock of seeing you after all
these years could kill her.

268
00:20:44.004 --> 00:20:45.004
Arthur?

269
00:20:47.585 --> 00:20:49.141
Well. come here.

270
00:21:06.264 --> 00:21:07.867
This is unexpected.

271
00:21:10.618 --> 00:21:13.125
- Mother. what's happened to you?
- As you see.

272
00:21:13.245 --> 00:21:15.427
I have lost the use of my limbs.

273
00:21:15.699 --> 00:21:18.361
I have not been outside
these doors for...

274
00:21:18.947 --> 00:21:20.643
Tell him for how long.

275
00:21:21.257 --> 00:21:23.087
A dozen year next Christmas.

276
00:21:27.670 --> 00:21:30.280
Mother. I am afraid I've come back
in unhappy circumstances.

277
00:21:30.440 --> 00:21:32.520
- Is the business in trouble?
- No.

278
00:21:33.637 --> 00:21:35.562
No. May we speak in private?

279
00:21:46.492 --> 00:21:48.937
Mother. I must ask you
to prepare yourself.

280
00:21:49.525 --> 00:21:52.229
Father passed away some
three months ago. an apoplexy.

281
00:21:52.349 --> 00:21:53.949
He didn't suffer long.

282
00:21:55.466 --> 00:21:57.745
You need not have come half way
round the world

283
00:21:57.865 --> 00:22:00.215
to tell me that you could have written.

284
00:22:02.419 --> 00:22:03.867
I needed to see you.

285
00:22:05.608 --> 00:22:07.369
I wanted to give you this.

286
00:22:16.835 --> 00:22:19.600
Father was most insistent that
I put it in your hand myself.

287
00:22:24.362 --> 00:22:27.027
- Mother. what does it mean?
- Nothing.

288
00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:28.547
It means nothing.

289
00:22:29.899 --> 00:22:32.547
Affery?! Mr Arthur is retiring.

290
00:22:33.201 --> 00:22:34.840
Affery will show you to your room.

291
00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:38.040
Mother. you can't dismiss me.
There are things I need to know.

292
00:22:38.200 --> 00:22:40.707
Not this evening.
Come to me tomorrow at ten.

293
00:22:46.560 --> 00:22:49.351
<i>Don't kiss me. Only touch my hand.</i>

294
00:23:00.160 --> 00:23:01.294
Goodnight.

295
00:23:50.907 --> 00:23:52.627
<i>And here we are!</i>

296
00:23:53.047 --> 00:23:56.954
<i>Home sweet home!
And not a finer place to be found</i>

297
00:23:57.074 --> 00:23:59.813
<i>in the whole country
than dear old Twickenham!</i>

298
00:23:59.933 --> 00:24:03.445
Eh. Tattycoram?
So come on. down we get!

299
00:24:05.110 --> 00:24:07.403
And down we get. Mrs Meagles!

300
00:24:08.729 --> 00:24:10.307
Down we get. Pet!

301
00:24:11.015 --> 00:24:14.147
- Ah. and here's Poyner.
- Welcome home. sir!

302
00:24:14.400 --> 00:24:16.167
And how do we look to you. Poyner?

303
00:24:16.287 --> 00:24:19.582
Oh. very well. sir.
and very welcome too!

304
00:24:20.525 --> 00:24:22.147
<i>Be careful up there!</i>

305
00:24:22.500 --> 00:24:25.071
If you please. sir. Mr Gowan called.

306
00:24:25.191 --> 00:24:28.067
not half an hour ago.
asking after Miss Pet. sir.

307
00:24:29.106 --> 00:24:31.929
Mr Gowan. I see. yes.
Did he leave any message?

308
00:24:32.049 --> 00:24:34.691
Only that he'd call again
tomorrow morning. sir.

309
00:24:34.811 --> 00:24:38.027
Very well. then. Let's go in.
Mrs Meagles.

310
00:24:40.115 --> 00:24:43.347
<i>- Poyner. what did Mr Gowan say?
- Well. what did you expect. Meagles?</i>

311
00:24:43.467 --> 00:24:46.347
3 months abroad would
cure her passion for him?

312
00:24:46.600 --> 00:24:47.986
Not hers. but his.

313
00:24:48.405 --> 00:24:50.800
I thought a scoundrel like
that would have less patience.

314
00:24:50.920 --> 00:24:54.468
Meagles! Mr Gowan isn't
a scoundrel. he's a gentleman!

315
00:24:55.561 --> 00:24:57.387
Same thing. often enough.

316
00:25:00.133 --> 00:25:01.253
Come along.

317
00:25:05.067 --> 00:25:06.913
She was never strong.

318
00:25:07.827 --> 00:25:09.642
I should never have...

319
00:25:11.019 --> 00:25:12.288
Too late now.

320
00:25:12.693 --> 00:25:13.693
Father?

321
00:25:15.044 --> 00:25:16.720
I wasn't asleep. you know?

322
00:25:17.326 --> 00:25:19.805
Just musing upon happier times.

323
00:25:20.398 --> 00:25:21.804
Happier times.

324
00:25:27.118 --> 00:25:29.360
<i>- Hello. Pa! Hello. Amy.
- Tip!</i>

325
00:25:30.028 --> 00:25:32.947
Call him Edward. Amy.
That's his proper name.

326
00:25:33.200 --> 00:25:34.310
How are you. my boy?

327
00:25:34.430 --> 00:25:37.667
Oh. not so bad. Pa. not so bad.
Thought I'd look in on you.

328
00:25:37.920 --> 00:25:40.720
Very good of you. Edward.
to think of your old father.

329
00:25:40.914 --> 00:25:43.315
Amy's always coming
and going these days.

330
00:25:43.435 --> 00:25:45.890
Matter of fact. I'm thinking
of staying a while.

331
00:25:46.010 --> 00:25:47.640
Glad to hear it. my boy.

332
00:25:52.529 --> 00:25:55.532
- What's the matter. Tip?
- Nothing's the matter.

333
00:25:55.787 --> 00:25:56.931
Not exactly.

334
00:25:57.698 --> 00:25:59.586
Have you lost that job
at the law stationers?

335
00:25:59.706 --> 00:26:01.479
That one? I didn't like it there. Amy.

336
00:26:01.599 --> 00:26:05.387
I got tired of it. so I cut it.
Got another place in the fruit trade.

337
00:26:06.651 --> 00:26:09.827
Cut that. Then I got another
job in the horse dealing line.

338
00:26:10.375 --> 00:26:11.912
I did like that.

339
00:26:12.826 --> 00:26:16.416
but it didn't like me. So here
I am again. like the bad penny.

340
00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:18.630
Oh. Tip. don't say
that you're a prisoner.

341
00:26:18.750 --> 00:26:21.880
Well. I don't want to say it.
but what am I supposed to do?

342
00:26:22.227 --> 00:26:24.971
- I'm in for forty pound odd.
- Forty pounds!

343
00:26:25.708 --> 00:26:28.935
Looking on the bright side.
at least I know the ropes.

344
00:26:29.245 --> 00:26:32.862
Don't worry about me. Amy.
A little rest'll do me good!

345
00:26:32.982 --> 00:26:34.991
I shall do very well here.

346
00:26:36.311 --> 00:26:37.681
- Tip!
- What?

347
00:26:38.667 --> 00:26:41.107
Whatever you do. don't let father know.

348
00:27:29.040 --> 00:27:32.896
<i>Eyes down! Eat the food the good
Lord provided and be thankful.</i>

349
00:27:33.387 --> 00:27:36.547
<i>And remember. he is here
in this very room</i>

350
00:27:37.007 --> 00:27:40.735
<i>and knows every wicked thought you
think you keep hidden in your heart.</i>

351
00:27:42.000 --> 00:27:44.015
<i>- Do you hear me. Arthur?
- Yes. Mother.</i>

352
00:27:44.135 --> 00:27:48.008
<i>Yes. Mother. Do you know. I believe
you are no better than your father.</i>

353
00:27:49.873 --> 00:27:51.827
<i>Look me in the eyes. Arthur!</i>

354
00:27:54.155 --> 00:27:56.467
<i>Yes. You are a vessel of sin.
I believe.</i>

355
00:27:56.720 --> 00:27:59.307
<i>just like your father was and still is.</i>

356
00:28:00.229 --> 00:28:03.320
<i>And you will bring me nothing
but shame and disappointment.</i>

357
00:28:03.769 --> 00:28:05.318
<i>just as he has.</i>

358
00:28:21.130 --> 00:28:22.809
There we are. Arthur.

359
00:28:23.187 --> 00:28:25.532
I brought you a nice cup of tea.

360
00:28:25.827 --> 00:28:27.547
Oh. thank you. Affery.

361
00:28:29.403 --> 00:28:31.107
He's down there with her.

362
00:28:31.227 --> 00:28:34.376
Them two clever ones.
putting their heads together.

363
00:28:35.147 --> 00:28:38.667
She wants you to go down
to her at ten. not before.

364
00:28:42.069 --> 00:28:45.426
I can't tell you how glad I am to see
you back in your own bed. Arthur.

365
00:28:45.546 --> 00:28:47.425
I wish I could say the same. Affery.

366
00:28:47.545 --> 00:28:50.005
but it is very good to see you again.

367
00:28:50.708 --> 00:28:53.110
So you... you are Mrs Flintwinch now?

368
00:28:53.230 --> 00:28:55.160
- I am.
- How did that come about?

369
00:28:56.690 --> 00:28:59.243
Well. I hardly know myself. Arthur.

370
00:29:00.720 --> 00:29:04.270
Them two clever ones arranged
it all between them. I believe.

371
00:29:05.920 --> 00:29:07.543
He never courted me. you know.

372
00:29:07.663 --> 00:29:10.501
"Affery." he said. "What do you
think of the name Flintwinch?"

373
00:29:10.621 --> 00:29:12.648
"What do I think?." I said.
"Yes." he said.

374
00:29:12.768 --> 00:29:16.411
"Because you're gonna take it.
You and me must be married."

375
00:29:16.531 --> 00:29:20.208
"So if you put your bonnet on tomorrow
morning at eight. we'll get it over."

376
00:29:20.328 --> 00:29:22.667
He'd had the banns read and everything.

377
00:29:22.904 --> 00:29:25.702
And she was all for it. Lord knows why.

378
00:29:26.267 --> 00:29:28.947
So what could I say
when it had got to that?

379
00:29:29.359 --> 00:29:30.709
If it had been...

380
00:29:31.132 --> 00:29:33.303
if it had been a smothering
instead of a wedding.

381
00:29:33.423 --> 00:29:35.550
I don't think I could have said
anything against it.

382
00:29:35.670 --> 00:29:39.387
- not against them two clever ones.
- And are you happy. Affery?

383
00:29:39.507 --> 00:29:40.507
Happy?

384
00:29:41.507 --> 00:29:43.390
What's happy got to do with it?

385
00:29:45.650 --> 00:29:48.403
<i>- Affery!
- There's Jeremiah on the stairs!</i>

386
00:29:48.523 --> 00:29:50.391
<i>- Where are you hiding?
- I'm here!</i>

387
00:29:50.511 --> 00:29:52.791
<i>- I'm here. Jeremiah.
-I shan't ask you again!</i>

388
00:29:52.911 --> 00:29:53.986
<i>Oh. Lord...</i>

389
00:31:20.145 --> 00:31:21.851
Ah. there you are. Amy.

390
00:31:21.971 --> 00:31:23.507
Punctual as usual!

391
00:31:23.760 --> 00:31:25.226
And how are you today?

392
00:31:25.346 --> 00:31:27.473
Very well. thank you. Mrs Clennam.
And yourself?

393
00:31:27.593 --> 00:31:31.147
I endure what I must. Amy.
I don't complain.

394
00:31:32.562 --> 00:31:34.314
Come here and sit by me.

395
00:31:45.915 --> 00:31:48.190
- Arthur's waiting.
- Let him wait.

396
00:31:48.310 --> 00:31:50.951
He may come up at ten o'clock.
as arranged.

397
00:31:51.787 --> 00:31:54.265
I hope your father is well. my dear.

398
00:31:54.385 --> 00:31:56.706
He's quite well.
thank you. Mrs Clennam.

399
00:32:12.889 --> 00:32:14.154
<i>Arthur...</i>

400
00:32:17.284 --> 00:32:19.095
<i>Your mother. Arthur.</i>

401
00:32:21.093 --> 00:32:22.234
<i>Put it right.</i>

402
00:32:33.726 --> 00:32:34.960
She'll see you now.

403
00:32:46.553 --> 00:32:47.760
Here he is.

404
00:32:48.512 --> 00:32:49.974
All right. Jeremiah.

405
00:32:50.094 --> 00:32:51.712
I shan't need you.

406
00:33:01.669 --> 00:33:03.877
- Well?
- I've made up my mind

407
00:33:03.997 --> 00:33:05.871
to leave the business. Mother.

408
00:33:06.259 --> 00:33:08.859
I've given almost
half my life to it so far.

409
00:33:09.432 --> 00:33:11.600
I felt that I owed you
and my father that much.

410
00:33:12.447 --> 00:33:13.447
And now...

411
00:33:14.432 --> 00:33:15.452
I consider

412
00:33:15.965 --> 00:33:18.518
that I have discharged my debt.

413
00:33:20.032 --> 00:33:21.552
I felt like a prisoner.

414
00:33:22.811 --> 00:33:24.512
Now I claim my freedom.

415
00:33:27.197 --> 00:33:31.027
Have you finished. Arthur.
or have you anything further to say?

416
00:33:35.841 --> 00:33:37.849
Er... there is something else.

417
00:33:38.539 --> 00:33:41.081
What I have said concerned myself.

418
00:33:41.512 --> 00:33:44.176
- This concerns us all.
- "Us all?"

419
00:33:44.439 --> 00:33:46.821
- "Us all?" Who are "us all?"
- Yourself.

420
00:33:47.803 --> 00:33:50.872
- myself. my dead father.
- Well?

421
00:33:54.073 --> 00:33:55.106
The watch...

422
00:33:56.945 --> 00:33:59.486
it meant something
but I don't know what.

423
00:34:00.886 --> 00:34:02.014
Father died

424
00:34:02.487 --> 00:34:04.783
without telling me what it meant.

425
00:34:05.063 --> 00:34:07.533
but over and over
and over before he died

426
00:34:07.653 --> 00:34:10.497
he pressed it into my hand saying.
"Your mother.

427
00:34:11.684 --> 00:34:13.500
"Your mother. Arthur.

428
00:34:14.392 --> 00:34:15.689
"Put it right."

429
00:34:17.296 --> 00:34:20.352
You oversaw all his dealings.
What did he mean. Mother?

430
00:34:20.602 --> 00:34:22.559
- What have we done?
- How dare you!

431
00:34:24.081 --> 00:34:26.268
Did it ever occur to you that he might
have had any

432
00:34:26.388 --> 00:34:28.800
secret remembrance
that caused him remorse?

433
00:34:28.960 --> 00:34:31.672
Our family business was always
driving hard bargains.

434
00:34:31.792 --> 00:34:34.019
and grasping at money.
Might it be possible that he...

435
00:34:34.139 --> 00:34:36.240
he wronged someone and made
no reparation for it?

436
00:34:36.400 --> 00:34:39.559
Flintwinch! Flintwinch!
Come here immediately!

437
00:34:39.679 --> 00:34:42.040
If we have wronged someone
and reparation can be made.

438
00:34:42.308 --> 00:34:44.280
let us know it and make it.
Let me make it.

439
00:34:44.514 --> 00:34:46.814
What? You're hammer and
tongs already. are you?

440
00:34:46.934 --> 00:34:49.378
I thought as much. What's the matter?

441
00:34:49.498 --> 00:34:51.112
My son. Flintwinch.

442
00:34:51.319 --> 00:34:53.451
has seen fit to lay aspersions

443
00:34:53.571 --> 00:34:56.072
and accusations on his own father.

444
00:34:56.279 --> 00:34:59.312
Oh. dear.
That's not dutiful. Mr Arthur.

445
00:34:59.520 --> 00:35:01.528
This is none of your business.
Flintwinch.

446
00:35:01.648 --> 00:35:03.902
Oh. ain't it? But I say it is.

447
00:35:04.471 --> 00:35:08.272
Has young Arthur told you what
he means to do about the business?

448
00:35:08.588 --> 00:35:10.592
He has relinquished it!

449
00:35:11.428 --> 00:35:13.803
Thereby giving me the pleasure

450
00:35:13.923 --> 00:35:16.592
of advancing
an old and faithful servant.

451
00:35:17.646 --> 00:35:21.552
Jeremiah. the captain
has deserted the ship.

452
00:35:22.275 --> 00:35:25.272
You and I will sink or float with it.

453
00:35:25.607 --> 00:35:27.174
Excellent. ma'am.

454
00:35:27.900 --> 00:35:29.560
I thank you with all my heart.

455
00:35:30.488 --> 00:35:32.352
Right. time for your oysters!

456
00:35:36.146 --> 00:35:39.312
You may leave us.
You have no further business here.

457
00:35:43.543 --> 00:35:46.232
- Goodbye. Mother.
- Only touch my hand.

458
00:35:50.209 --> 00:35:51.209
Now go.

459
00:35:58.152 --> 00:36:01.507
Ah. Amy. Good girl.

460
00:36:02.241 --> 00:36:04.712
Don't be shy. come closer.

461
00:36:15.258 --> 00:36:16.440
Thank you. Amy.

462
00:36:19.988 --> 00:36:23.032
What do you still do here?
You are not wanted!

463
00:36:37.272 --> 00:36:39.553
Oh. Arthur! You gave me a start!

464
00:36:39.673 --> 00:36:42.629
Tell me. Affery. who is that
young girl that I saw upstairs?

465
00:36:42.749 --> 00:36:44.919
Little Dorrit? Oh. she's nothing.

466
00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:48.909
She's a whim of hers. just an object
of her charity. that's all.

467
00:36:49.029 --> 00:36:51.112
My mother was never given
to charity before.

468
00:36:51.232 --> 00:36:53.520
Is she a connection of ours?
Do we know her family?

469
00:36:54.600 --> 00:36:56.503
Have you taken a fancy to her?

470
00:36:57.729 --> 00:37:01.640
You must have had your pick of girls
out there. across the China Sea.

471
00:37:01.872 --> 00:37:03.871
There were one or two. Affery.

472
00:37:05.561 --> 00:37:07.174
Oh. here you are. Amy.

473
00:37:08.830 --> 00:37:11.545
Sit down and eat it.
Keep your strength up.

474
00:37:13.504 --> 00:37:16.832
- Do you remember your old sweetheart?
- Yes. I do. very well.

475
00:37:17.040 --> 00:37:18.960
And I remember how we were separated.

476
00:37:19.120 --> 00:37:21.559
Well. she's a widow now. and well to do.

477
00:37:21.814 --> 00:37:24.386
and if you'd like to have her.
you can. so there!

478
00:37:24.506 --> 00:37:26.759
You're a man of the world now. Arthur.

479
00:37:27.010 --> 00:37:29.679
you could have your pick
of any girl you wanted.

480
00:37:39.021 --> 00:37:42.938
Ah! Home. sweet home!
Nothing to beat it!

481
00:37:43.406 --> 00:37:45.152
What do you say. Tattycoram?

482
00:37:45.272 --> 00:37:47.072
Nothing at all. Mr Meagles.

483
00:37:47.360 --> 00:37:50.480
Nothing at all! But you feel as
I do. I know you do. I know it!

484
00:37:51.216 --> 00:37:54.245
You think you do. but in truth
you know nothing at all.

485
00:37:55.456 --> 00:37:57.417
Fiddlesticks! Bother!

486
00:37:57.537 --> 00:37:59.458
Oh. what's the matter. my dear?

487
00:37:59.655 --> 00:38:01.896
Only that I've left
my umbrella upstairs.

488
00:38:02.016 --> 00:38:05.232
Oh. well. never mind. dear.
Tattycoram'll fetch it for you

489
00:38:05.352 --> 00:38:07.832
and happy to do so.
aren't you. Tattycoram?

490
00:38:09.217 --> 00:38:12.340
I'll fetch it if you wish. but
I don't know what makes you think I'm

491
00:38:12.460 --> 00:38:15.016
happy to fetch and carry
and look after you all

492
00:38:15.136 --> 00:38:17.785
when no-one will fetch
and carry and look after me!

493
00:38:17.905 --> 00:38:21.112
Temper. temper!
Count to five and twenty. Tattycoram!

494
00:38:21.918 --> 00:38:24.552
I can't! It's too late!
I'm beyond myself!

495
00:38:24.779 --> 00:38:25.912
Tattycoram!

496
00:38:26.212 --> 00:38:27.760
Best let her go. Meagles.

497
00:38:28.406 --> 00:38:30.425
She'll come to herself by and by.

498
00:38:30.545 --> 00:38:32.396
Yes. mustn't worry.

499
00:38:33.278 --> 00:38:35.232
Oh. well played. Pet!

500
00:38:37.440 --> 00:38:40.592
I can't bear it. I can't. I can't!

501
00:38:40.712 --> 00:38:44.253
Oh. Lord what's the matter with me.
why am I such a wicked girl?

502
00:38:46.960 --> 00:38:49.352
- Good afternoon. Harriet.
- What...

503
00:38:49.766 --> 00:38:51.120
What are you doing here?

504
00:38:51.280 --> 00:38:53.912
I was on my way to see you.
You didn't write.

505
00:38:54.883 --> 00:38:56.672
I was worried about you.

506
00:39:01.480 --> 00:39:02.480
No.

507
00:39:03.879 --> 00:39:05.360
No. I won't talk to you.

508
00:39:06.457 --> 00:39:09.347
- I mustn't!
- Oh. but I think you will. Harriet.

509
00:39:09.712 --> 00:39:11.054
I think you must.

510
00:39:16.095 --> 00:39:18.428
And so the day of reckoning!

511
00:39:19.878 --> 00:39:23.667
Rigaud is to face
the full majesty of the court.

512
00:39:24.392 --> 00:39:26.948
And I shall triumph. I believe.

513
00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:30.577
Their witnesses will melt away.
their evidence

514
00:39:30.697 --> 00:39:32.240
will crumble into dust.

515
00:39:32.400 --> 00:39:34.381
Sens'altro. signore. sens'altro.

516
00:39:34.796 --> 00:39:37.443
- Monsieur Rigaud.
- Ah. Monsieur le Jailer.

517
00:39:37.563 --> 00:39:40.390
The President of the Court has
decided there is not enough evidence

518
00:39:40.510 --> 00:39:44.472
to convict you and you are free to
go. but there is a crowd out there.

519
00:39:44.709 --> 00:39:47.536
- and they don't love you.
- Rabble! I despise them.

520
00:39:47.833 --> 00:39:51.112
I suggest you get as far away
from here as you can.

521
00:39:51.652 --> 00:39:54.352
- Monsieur Rigaud. time to go!
- Cavalletto...

522
00:39:56.436 --> 00:39:59.813
You and I will meet again one day.

523
00:40:01.823 --> 00:40:02.952
I believe.

524
00:40:03.072 --> 00:40:05.326
And what will I do with you then? Huh?

525
00:40:06.107 --> 00:40:07.488
Eat you. perhaps.

526
00:40:10.870 --> 00:40:12.620
- Altro. altro.
- Altro.

527
00:40:15.121 --> 00:40:16.121
Altro.

528
00:40:16.293 --> 00:40:18.220
Lead on. monsieur le jailer!

529
00:40:19.848 --> 00:40:23.752
<i># Qu'est-ce qui passe ici si tard.
compagnons de la marjolaine</i>

530
00:40:23.960 --> 00:40:26.392
<i># Qu'est-ce qui passe ici si tard?</i>

531
00:40:26.733 --> 00:40:28.392
<i># Gai. gai. gai... #</i>

532
00:40:31.832 --> 00:40:34.667
<i># Qu'est-ce qui passe
ici si tard... #</i>

533
00:40:34.787 --> 00:40:36.658
Curse on this poxy weather!

534
00:40:39.041 --> 00:40:41.432
Rigaud is down for now. never mind.

535
00:40:42.799 --> 00:40:44.749
Rigaud will rise again.

536
00:40:46.422 --> 00:40:48.792
Monsieur! Monsieur. arr�t!

537
00:40:49.391 --> 00:40:53.032
Pour le nom de dieu! Salaud! Cochon!

538
00:40:53.403 --> 00:40:56.165
May your nethers rot off in strips!

539
00:40:57.557 --> 00:40:59.136
Attends! J'arrive!

540
00:40:59.512 --> 00:41:01.406
J'arrive. Monsieur! Merci!

541
00:41:04.024 --> 00:41:05.138
Allez!

542
00:41:53.738 --> 00:41:55.552
<i>- Hello. John.
- Miss Amy...</i>

543
00:41:57.440 --> 00:42:01.184
<i>- I picked up a little something.
- Thank you. John. I should go up now.</i>

544
00:42:09.703 --> 00:42:11.827
- Good evening.
- Oh. good evening.

545
00:42:12.892 --> 00:42:16.408
I... I wonder. could you... could you
tell me. what place is this?

546
00:42:16.867 --> 00:42:20.814
- This place? Well. it's the Marshalsea.
- The debtors' prison?

547
00:42:20.934 --> 00:42:23.021
That's it. sir. yes.
Yes. the debtors' prison.

548
00:42:23.141 --> 00:42:25.749
I... I beg your pardon.
Can anyone go in there?

549
00:42:25.869 --> 00:42:28.653
Oh. yes. yes. Anyone may go in. sir.

550
00:42:28.978 --> 00:42:31.125
It's not everyone who may go out.

551
00:42:32.200 --> 00:42:34.072
May I walk in with you?

552
00:42:35.940 --> 00:42:38.099
I should count it an honour. sir.

553
00:42:39.491 --> 00:42:41.278
Thank you. Mr Chivery.

554
00:42:41.398 --> 00:42:42.496
Frederick.

555
00:42:44.560 --> 00:42:48.558
Er. just... do you know anyone that
lives here by the name of Dorrit?

556
00:42:49.672 --> 00:42:53.272
- My name is Dorrit. Frederick Dorrit.
- Do you live here?

557
00:42:53.660 --> 00:42:56.887
Not as an inmate.
never as an... er... as an inmate.

558
00:42:57.512 --> 00:43:00.717
My brother William Dorrit
is in residence here.

559
00:43:00.837 --> 00:43:03.640
Ah. I beg your pardon.
I had no idea. Let me explain.

560
00:43:03.800 --> 00:43:06.613
I have recently come back
from a long absence overseas.

561
00:43:06.733 --> 00:43:09.498
I have seen a young woman
who works at my mother's house.

562
00:43:09.618 --> 00:43:13.080
Mrs Clennam in the City. This young
woman I know only as Little Dorrit.

563
00:43:13.240 --> 00:43:15.466
I saw her come in at these
gates not five minutes ago.

564
00:43:15.586 --> 00:43:18.004
The young woman whom you saw
is my brother's child.

565
00:43:18.124 --> 00:43:21.000
Ah. I should like to know more
about her. and to help her. if I can.

566
00:43:21.680 --> 00:43:25.112
Help her. sir?
Does not your mother help her?

567
00:43:26.433 --> 00:43:29.992
Oh. I assure you sir. I have
no ignoble designs upon her.

568
00:43:32.921 --> 00:43:36.752
Well. if you wish. you may
come with me. Thank you.

569
00:43:42.369 --> 00:43:44.005
Very kind of young John.

570
00:43:44.125 --> 00:43:47.810
A very handsome consideration.
delicately expressed.

571
00:43:48.510 --> 00:43:51.392
I hope you showed him
proper thanks. Amy.

572
00:43:53.044 --> 00:43:56.211
William. this gentleman is Mr Clennam.

573
00:43:56.331 --> 00:43:58.632
son of Mrs Clennam.

574
00:43:58.893 --> 00:44:02.352
Amy's... friend.
He wishes to pay his respects.

575
00:44:02.560 --> 00:44:05.192
Mr Clennam. you do me honour. sir.

576
00:44:05.312 --> 00:44:06.912
Frederick. my chair.

577
00:44:07.032 --> 00:44:09.196
Pray. pray sit down. Mr Clennam.

578
00:44:10.890 --> 00:44:13.560
You are welcome to the Marshalsea.

579
00:44:14.151 --> 00:44:18.109
Yes. I've welcomed many
fine gentlemen here.

580
00:44:18.229 --> 00:44:20.840
Perhaps you're aware -
my daughter may have mentioned it -

581
00:44:21.227 --> 00:44:24.752
that I am known as
The Father of the Marshalsea.

582
00:44:25.090 --> 00:44:27.025
An honorary title. to be sure.

583
00:44:27.145 --> 00:44:29.832
but one that gives me
much gratification.

584
00:44:30.040 --> 00:44:32.143
- Father!
- You know. I dare say.

585
00:44:32.263 --> 00:44:35.520
- that my daughter Amy was born here?
- No. No. I did not. sir.

586
00:44:35.680 --> 00:44:38.080
- Some might think that a disgrace.
- No. indeed.

587
00:44:38.344 --> 00:44:41.632
She's a good girl. sir. a dear girl.
Amy. put the dish down.

588
00:44:42.072 --> 00:44:45.552
Would you do me the honour. sir.
of sharing my humble repast?

589
00:44:45.992 --> 00:44:48.152
No... Not a morsel. I have dined.

590
00:44:49.392 --> 00:44:53.304
My elder daughter Fanny. does not
live with me. but with my bro...

591
00:44:53.921 --> 00:44:56.632
What have you done
with Fanny. Frederick?

592
00:44:57.339 --> 00:45:00.072
Erm... believe she's out
walking with Tip.

593
00:45:00.795 --> 00:45:01.795
Edward!

594
00:45:02.045 --> 00:45:06.042
Edward! Have the goodness
to use the correct nomenclature.

595
00:45:06.600 --> 00:45:09.317
My son Edward. Mr Clennam.

596
00:45:09.437 --> 00:45:12.399
he's a little wild.
but he's a good lad at heart.

597
00:45:12.782 --> 00:45:16.202
- Your first visit here. sir?
- Yes. my very first. Mr Dorrit.

598
00:45:16.426 --> 00:45:18.357
I wonder. could I ask you.

599
00:45:19.000 --> 00:45:22.999
before your arrival here. did you have
any business with the House of Clennam?

600
00:45:23.746 --> 00:45:24.768
Clennam?

601
00:45:28.792 --> 00:45:31.918
No. you. sir. are the first Clennam

602
00:45:32.038 --> 00:45:34.072
it's been my pleasure to meet.

603
00:45:34.280 --> 00:45:36.656
Though I've welcomed
many fine gentlemen here.

604
00:45:36.776 --> 00:45:39.693
Amy. what was the name of the
gentleman from Camberwell

605
00:45:39.813 --> 00:45:42.174
- who was here last Sunday?
- I can't recall. Father.

606
00:45:42.294 --> 00:45:44.428
Oh. of course you can.
of course you can.

607
00:45:44.548 --> 00:45:48.235
The one who performed that handsome
action with so much delicacy.

608
00:45:48.355 --> 00:45:51.258
Oh. tush! His name has quite escaped me.

609
00:45:51.378 --> 00:45:53.152
But. as I was saying Mr Clennam.

610
00:45:53.272 --> 00:45:56.032
a handsome and delicate action.

611
00:45:56.240 --> 00:45:58.472
you might like to know what it was.

612
00:45:59.832 --> 00:46:01.405
Yes. yes. indeed.

613
00:46:01.792 --> 00:46:05.541
You. you. you must know. Mr Clennam.
that it does sometimes occur

614
00:46:05.661 --> 00:46:09.589
to a gentlemen. er... who come here.
to offer some small...

615
00:46:09.709 --> 00:46:12.837
testimonial
to the Father of the Marshalsea.

616
00:46:12.957 --> 00:46:14.869
Sometimes it takes one shape.

617
00:46:14.989 --> 00:46:18.152
and sometimes another.
but it's generally...

618
00:46:19.232 --> 00:46:20.232
Money.

619
00:46:21.797 --> 00:46:22.880
- I see.
- Now.

620
00:46:23.040 --> 00:46:24.699
the gentleman from Camberwell.

621
00:46:24.819 --> 00:46:26.960
made a gesture of peculiar delicacy...

622
00:46:28.312 --> 00:46:30.311
He brought a bunch of geraniums;

623
00:46:30.431 --> 00:46:34.316
gardens not being accessible to me.
a bunch of geraniums.

624
00:46:34.436 --> 00:46:36.992
which. upon closer inspection.

625
00:46:37.573 --> 00:46:40.872
was found to contain a twist of paper.

626
00:46:42.067 --> 00:46:44.392
with two guineas inside!

627
00:46:44.600 --> 00:46:46.792
A handsome and delicate action...

628
00:46:47.500 --> 00:46:49.920
- I was never more pleased.
- Father. please stop.

629
00:46:50.193 --> 00:46:52.792
- Mr Clennam doesn't want to hear this.
- Oh. nonsense Amy.

630
00:46:52.912 --> 00:46:55.842
Mr Clennam and
I understand one other perfectly.

631
00:46:55.962 --> 00:46:57.977
- I believe.
- I should say so.

632
00:47:26.504 --> 00:47:28.472
What does she want now?

633
00:47:29.417 --> 00:47:31.552
Her and her blasted stick...

634
00:47:33.393 --> 00:47:35.308
Downstairs there's a wooden box

635
00:47:35.428 --> 00:47:39.386
containing legal documents and other
papers. You know the one I mean.

636
00:47:39.613 --> 00:47:41.377
- I do.
- Bring them to me.

637
00:47:41.497 --> 00:47:44.214
I want to see them destroyed.
Flintwinch.

638
00:47:44.800 --> 00:47:47.039
Destroyed. not hidden.

639
00:47:47.959 --> 00:47:49.015
Understood.

640
00:47:50.032 --> 00:47:53.241
It's imperative that my son
should never see them.

641
00:47:53.476 --> 00:47:54.649
Understood.

642
00:47:54.913 --> 00:47:56.897
Understood and all in hand.

643
00:47:57.702 --> 00:47:58.702
Good.

644
00:49:00.895 --> 00:49:04.407
And he was a very distinguished
gentleman. and was kind enough

645
00:49:04.527 --> 00:49:07.991
to leave a little testimonial.
which he managed with

646
00:49:08.111 --> 00:49:09.889
- great delicacy.
- I'm sure he did.

647
00:49:10.009 --> 00:49:12.717
Er... do you happen
to know where Miss Dorrit has gone?

648
00:49:12.837 --> 00:49:14.489
I'd like a word with her before I leave.

649
00:49:14.609 --> 00:49:17.055
She should be here!
She's away far too much.

650
00:49:17.175 --> 00:49:19.112
And as for my other children...

651
00:49:19.836 --> 00:49:22.448
Ah my dears!
I was just speaking of you.

652
00:49:22.568 --> 00:49:25.615
Mr Clennam. may I present
my elder daughter Fanny.

653
00:49:25.735 --> 00:49:27.096
and my son Edward.

654
00:49:28.352 --> 00:49:31.723
The bell. ah yes. that's a signal
for visitors to.

655
00:49:31.843 --> 00:49:32.913
er... retire.

656
00:49:33.033 --> 00:49:35.072
Fanny's come to say goodbye.

657
00:49:35.192 --> 00:49:37.272
Don't be alarmed.
there's plenty of time.

658
00:49:37.392 --> 00:49:39.580
plenty of time before
the gate is locked.

659
00:49:39.700 --> 00:49:41.361
How do you do.
Miss Dorrit. Mr Dorrit?

660
00:49:41.481 --> 00:49:44.820
Charmed. I'm sure. I only came to
get my clean dress from Amy. father.

661
00:49:44.940 --> 00:49:47.920
- Where is she gone?
- Here I am. here's your dress. Fanny.

662
00:49:48.192 --> 00:49:50.000
- It's mended and made up?
- Yes.

663
00:49:50.160 --> 00:49:52.120
- How about my waistcoat?
- Good girl.

664
00:49:52.280 --> 00:49:54.583
Come. Fanny. come now.
it's nearly time for the lock!

665
00:49:54.703 --> 00:49:57.032
All right. Uncle... Bye. Pa!

666
00:49:57.318 --> 00:50:00.160
Make haste. Mr Clennam.
'Less you want to spend the night here.

667
00:50:00.320 --> 00:50:04.076
I'll be with you directly.
Mr Dorrit. would you allow me...

668
00:50:06.392 --> 00:50:08.892
Mr Clennam. I'm... I'm deeply.

669
00:50:09.012 --> 00:50:11.592
- deeply moved.
- Please. Mr Dorrit. say no more.

670
00:50:11.712 --> 00:50:13.958
You must come and visit us again.

671
00:50:14.078 --> 00:50:16.116
Amy. show our friend the way.

672
00:50:19.732 --> 00:50:21.993
<i>All visitors time to leave.</i>

673
00:50:22.113 --> 00:50:24.566
<i>All out. please all out.</i>

674
00:50:32.280 --> 00:50:34.787
- There's the gate. Good evening. sir.
- Forgive me...

675
00:50:34.907 --> 00:50:38.655
- May we have a few words?
- Why did you follow me. sir?

676
00:50:38.943 --> 00:50:41.400
I could not speak to you in
private at my mother's house.

677
00:50:41.560 --> 00:50:43.371
You've seen how it is
between her and me.

678
00:50:43.491 --> 00:50:47.352
But I should like to ask you about my
mother's reasons for employing you.

679
00:50:47.916 --> 00:50:49.856
I believe your mother employed
me on merit.

680
00:50:49.976 --> 00:50:52.360
The bell will stop
and you'll be locked in. You must go.

681
00:50:52.520 --> 00:50:56.471
- May I speak with you again. Amy?
- Yes. I suppose so. How can I stop you?

682
00:50:56.624 --> 00:50:59.386
I'm sorry. I don't mean to be rude.
Good evening.

683
00:51:09.440 --> 00:51:11.906
Oh. I say? Could you open the gate?
I was delayed.

684
00:51:12.026 --> 00:51:14.679
Can't be done. sir.
more than me life's worth.

685
00:51:15.982 --> 00:51:17.862
You're here for the night now.

686
00:51:21.555 --> 00:51:22.646
Good God.

687
00:51:25.427 --> 00:51:27.678
Caught you. have they. Mr Clennam?

688
00:51:28.253 --> 00:51:30.957
You'll have to be sharper
than that next time.

689
00:51:31.389 --> 00:51:33.525
Er... surely you're locked in too.

690
00:51:34.447 --> 00:51:36.153
Why. so I am!

691
00:51:37.592 --> 00:51:38.800
But not in your way.

692
00:51:39.866 --> 00:51:43.320
I belong to the shop. only. er... the
guvnor's not supposed to know about it.

693
00:51:45.303 --> 00:51:47.000
Can I get any shelter here?

694
00:51:47.325 --> 00:51:51.232
Well. If you don't mind paying. they'll
make you up a bed in the snuggery.

695
00:51:52.427 --> 00:51:55.897
It ain't as snug as it sounds. mind.
Not like home.

696
00:51:56.017 --> 00:51:58.273
I'm sure it'll serve
well enough for one night.

697
00:51:58.393 --> 00:52:01.211
Come along then. Mr Clennam.
I'll see you all right.

698
00:52:01.331 --> 00:52:05.033
- Thank you.
- This way. Mr Clennam. This way.

699
00:52:28.455 --> 00:52:30.822
There. all gone.

700
00:52:33.245 --> 00:52:35.112
Thank you. Flintwinch.

701
00:53:06.811 --> 00:53:07.811
Jeremiah?

702
00:53:15.303 --> 00:53:16.394
<i>All clear.</i>

703
00:53:19.152 --> 00:53:20.220
Jeremiah?

704
00:53:28.879 --> 00:53:29.879
<i>Sit down.</i>

705
00:53:30.348 --> 00:53:32.843
<i>What about that glass
you said I could have?</i>

706
00:53:35.108 --> 00:53:36.108
<i>Here.</i>

707
00:53:37.948 --> 00:53:39.630
<i>Drink it. choke yourself.</i>

708
00:53:40.272 --> 00:53:42.007
<i>Mrs Clennam's port wine.</i>

709
00:53:43.995 --> 00:53:46.472
Very nice. her health.

710
00:53:50.283 --> 00:53:53.915
Your health. his health and
all friends round St Paul's.

711
00:53:57.465 --> 00:53:59.392
<i>Where's the box?</i>

712
00:54:00.240 --> 00:54:01.841
All here. Jeremiah.

713
00:54:09.206 --> 00:54:12.472
- Heavy enough.
- Take care. Guard it with your life.

714
00:54:21.241 --> 00:54:24.185
Affery! What are you about.
you silly old woman?

715
00:54:24.305 --> 00:54:28.158
You've been getting out
of bed in your sleep! Dreaming!

716
00:54:29.531 --> 00:54:31.330
You slip back up to bed.

717
00:54:31.544 --> 00:54:33.913
And if you ever have such a dream again.

718
00:54:34.033 --> 00:54:35.962
it's a sign you're in want of physic!

719
00:54:36.082 --> 00:54:39.367
And I'll give you such a dose.
old woman... Such a dose!

720
00:54:39.921 --> 00:54:41.371
Now. off with you!

721
00:54:49.948 --> 00:54:50.948
All clear.

722
00:55:00.570 --> 00:55:02.834
You guard it with your life. Ephraim.

723
00:55:03.444 --> 00:55:06.670
Yes. Jeremiah. safe with me.

724
00:55:07.305 --> 00:56:07.672
